{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is your question here?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "This is the answer to the question. Keep it clear and concise. You can include <strong>HTML formatting</strong> if needed."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does your product/service work?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Detailed answer explaining how the product or service works. Include specific details and examples."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What are your pricing options?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Explanation of pricing, including different tiers or options available."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you offer customer support?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Details about customer support availability, channels, and response times."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is your refund policy?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Clear explanation of refund or return policy, including timeframes and conditions."
      }
    }
  ]
}

<!-- 
INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Add as many question-answer pairs as needed (minimum 2 recommended)
2. Questions should match exactly what appears on your page
3. Answers should be visible on the page (not hidden content)
4. Keep answers focused and under 300 words each
5. You can use basic HTML in the answer text
6. Each question must have exactly one accepted answer

REQUIRED FIELDS:
- @context, @type, mainEntity (array of Question objects)
- Each Question needs: name, acceptedAnswer
- Each Answer needs: text

BEST PRACTICES:
- Use natural, conversational questions
- Include questions your customers actually ask
- Provide complete, helpful answers
- Keep questions and answers visible on the page
- Update as new common questions emerge

FAQ SCHEMA BENEFITS:
- Rich snippets in Google search results
- Featured in "People Also Ask" sections
- Improved AI platform understanding
- Better voice search results
- Enhanced user experience

IMPORTANT NOTES:
- Do NOT add questions that aren't on the page
- Do NOT use for promotional content
- Answers must be genuinely helpful
- Each question should have ONE clear answer
- Questions should be phrased as users would ask them

ADDING MORE QUESTIONS:
Simply copy this block and add to the mainEntity array:

    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Your question here?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Your answer here."
      }
    }

Remember to add a comma after each question block except the last one.
-->
